# Smart Energy Lighting System v2.0
## LD7182 — AI for IoT | Northumbria University London

### Project Overview
An AI-powered IoT system for intelligent indoor 
lighting control using distance-based false trigger 
prevention. The system activates lighting only when 
a person is genuinely entering a room (within 80cm), 
not merely passing by.

### Hardware Components
- ESP32-S3 microcontroller
- HC-SR04 ultrasonic distance sensor (GPIO 5 & 18)
- PIR motion sensor (GPIO 13)
- LDR ambient light sensor (GPIO 2)
- DHT22 temperature sensor (GPIO 15)
- LED output (GPIO 4)

### Repository Contents
- sketch.ino — Annotated Arduino source code
- diagram.json — Wokwi circuit diagram
- libraries.txt — Required libraries
- AI_for_IoT_Assessment.ipynb — ML Colab notebook
- smart_lighting_model.tflite — TFLite edge model
- smart_lighting_dataset_2024.csv — Training dataset
- confusion_matrix.png — ML evaluation results

